Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE is pleased to announce for sale, 483-487 Humphreys St, a .41 acre site in Nashville’s growing Wedgewood Houston neighborhood. Located directly south of downtown, the site is in close proximity and offers easy access to area amenities, Class A developments, and Nashville’s hottest neighborhoods.

Up-and-coming Wedgewood-Houston is a buzzing creative hub, with former factories converted into art spaces and studios. 483-487 Humphreys is a prime development site that is centrally located in this once industrial neighborhood. The proximity to downtown, affordable rents and real estate prices, and the number of old warehouses, factories and garages have attracted artists, musicians and entrepreneurs to open restaurants, distilleries, breweries, galleries, studios and workshops in the area. The highest and best use for 483-487 Humphreys Street is mixed-use zoning that would allow for 17,838 square feet of retail and/or workshops spanning across the first 2 floors and potentially an additional 2 floors of residential units for a total for 4 floors altogether. This would allow the buyer to maximize the FAR currently entitled on the land while providing the optimum benefit for the Wedgewood
Houston community.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: Located just north of I-40 loop and west of Downtown, the Nations neighborhood is buzzing with excitement. Situated far away enough from the hustle and bustle of Downtown yet close enough to the action, the Nations is an appealing area for renters and homeowners alike. The neighborhood benefits from quick accessibility to I-40 and is within close proximity to area universities. There are multiple shopping and dining options in the area including, but not limited to, 51 North Taproom, Frothy Monkey, The Mill Boutique, and the Nations Bar and Grill.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
The 1650 54th Ave N property is an ideal location for future development as its highest and best use is no longer for industrial application. The 10-acre site is ideally situated in the rapidly emerging Nations neighborhood just outside of Downtown Nashville and thus provides tremendous potential for urban infill development. 

The value of the site and its attractiveness to mixed-use developers will remain insulated from the current urban supply due to its location in the Nations neighborhood and its continued growth and evolution within the urban core. For-sale housing values in the area continue to soar, keeping pressure on renter demand. Appetite from developers should continue to benefit from the lack of future new supply in the immediate area and the natural and economic barriers to entry that now exist. There are several mixed-use projects close to starting construction in the immediate vicinity. However, this will allow for time to allow for stabilization and rent growth. The resulting demand for new product in the pipeline will be robust once the near-term projects stabilize.
